import '../../styles/global.css';

const faqs = [];
---

<Layout
  title="How to Convert Your Zoho Commerce Site Into A Mobile App"
  description="Learn how to turn your Zoho Commerce site into a mobile app with our step-by-step guide. Increase your reach and engagement with mobile users today!"
>
  <Nav />

  <section class="py-20 md:py-32 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <span class="text-sm font-semibold text-emerald-600 uppercase tracking-wider">Website Builders</span>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-4 mb-6">How to Convert Your Zoho Commerce Site Into A Mobile App</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-slate-600 mb-8">Learn how to turn your Zoho Commerce site into a mobile app with our step-by-step guide. Increase your reach and engagement with mobile users today!</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 px-4 bg-slate-50">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose prose-lg prose-slate">
      <p id>It’s a fact: mobile eCommerce is on the rise. </p><p id>More and more people are using their phones to shop, and if your eCommerce store isn’t optimized for mobile, you’re missing out on a huge chunk of potential revenue.</p><p id>But a mobile website alone isn't enough. All the top brands today have their own mobile apps.</p><p id>You, too, can build and launch an app for your Zoho Commerce store - and it won't cost you hundreds of thousands of dollars.</p><p id>If you want to grow your business and stay relevant in a mobile-first eCommerce landscape, keep reading, and we'll show you how to convert your Zoho Commerce store into a mobile app with&nbsp;<a href="https://www.mobiloud.com" id>MobiLoud</a>.</p><h2 id>Can You Create Mobile Apps with Zoho Commerce?</h2><p id>The Zoho Commerce platform is designed for websites.&nbsp;And the underlying technology is very different between a website and a mobile app.</p><p id>This means you'll need some help if you're going to create a mobile app for your Zoho Commerce store.</p><p id>You'll either need to build your app as a separate platform, and build an API to connect the mobile app to your Zoho&nbsp;Commerce backend.</p><p id>Or, you can use a service to <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/blog/convert-website-to-mobile-app" id>convert your website into a mobile app</a> - like <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/" id>MobiLoud</a>.</p><h3 id>What's the Best Way to Convert a Zoho Commerce Store Into an App?</h3><p id>The best way to turn your Zoho Commerce store into a mobile app is converting your site with MobiLoud.</p><p id>Ultimately, building a separate mobile app is too expensive, time-consuming, and comes with a lot of overhead.</p><p id>It can take anywhere from $50,000 to six figures plus to develop a mobile app.</p><p id>Time-wise, you're looking at six months to a year before you can launch.</p><p id>And then once you launch, you're stuck with an expensive platform to maintain. </p><blockquote id>“If we had unlimited time and money, we would probably go for a custom native app, but that is half a million to a million a year to maintain.”</blockquote><p id><em id>- David Cost,&nbsp;VP&nbsp;of eCommerce &amp;&nbsp;Marketing at&nbsp;</em><a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/customers/rainbow-shops" id><em id>Rainbow Shops</em></a></p><p id>Many businesses today turn to <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/blog/best-ecommerce-mobile-app-builder">eCommerce mobile app builders</a> instead of building natively.</p><p id>These tools offer a no-code development experience, allowing non-coders to build mobile apps relatively fast and inexpensively.</p><p id>But there are two major issues.</p><ol start="1" id><li id>While popular eCommerce platforms like <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/blog/best-shopify-mobile-app-builders" id>Shopify</a> have a vast ecosystem of tools and plugins, there are few app builders made to work with Zoho Commerce.</li><li id>Even if you can find an app builder for Zoho Commerce, these tools are limiting, and make it hard (if not impossible) to fully integrate all the features from your store into your apps.</li></ol><p id>A Zoho Commerce mobile app builder is not the way.</p><p id><a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/" id>MobiLoud</a>, however, gives you all the benefits of a no-code development tool, without the limitations, making it the best way to create a Zoho Commerce mobile app.</p><figure id class="w-richtext-figure-type-image w-richtext-align-fullwidth" style="max-width:1201px" data-rt-type="image" data-rt-align="fullwidth" data-rt-max-width="1201px"><a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/" target="_blank" id><div id><img src="https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/63894f0e251e567f6e443bfa/6865a4f4bddb577fbadbb7ee_20250702T0915-c3eb150a-4adb-4df4-9b01-dd6b37e8e702.webp" loading="lazy" alt="__wf_reserved_inherit" width="auto" height="auto" id></div></a></figure><h2 id>How to Turn Your Zoho Commerce Store into a Mobile App</h2><p id>With <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/" id>MobiLoud</a>, you can create a mobile app for your Zoho Commerce store in less than 30 days.</p><p id>MobiLoud is a service to turn any website into Android and iOS&nbsp;apps.</p><figure id class="w-richtext-figure-type-image w-richtext-align-fullwidth" style="max-width:2240px" data-rt-type="image" data-rt-align="fullwidth" data-rt-max-width="2240px"><div id><img src="https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/63894f0e251e567f6e443bfa/6865a570f06958243b49c111_20250702T0924-946bc16d-f079-4f1e-a8ab-a2b8d8507d94.webp" loading="lazy" alt="__wf_reserved_inherit" width="auto" height="auto" id></div><figcaption id>Just a few of the successful eCommerce apps we've built for high-revenue bran</figcaption></figure><p id>MobiLoud fully recreates the experience of your web store in the apps.&nbsp;Unlike drag-and-drop app builders, it doesn't use templates, pre-built blocks and API integrations.</p><p id>It shows a real, up-to-date, functional version of your website inside your app. It's fully synced with your store, for absolute consistency and easy maintenance.</p><p id>As long as your mobile website is fast and offers a great user experience, your app will do the same - but better, with the addition of UI elements that give it a native experience.</p><figure id class="w-richtext-figure-type-image w-richtext-align-fullwidth" style="max-width:800px" data-rt-type="image" data-rt-align="fullwidth" data-rt-max-width="800px"><div id><img src="https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/63894f0e251e567f6e443bfa/6865a4f411c5deea2720215b_20250702T0917-1cbe6e0e-c126-4762-9d49-bce8002c0360.webp" loading="lazy" alt="__wf_reserved_inherit" width="auto" height="auto" id></div><figcaption id>A mobile website (left) and what it will look like as an app&nbsp;(right)</figcaption></figure><p id>MobiLoud apps also have unlimited push notification functionality, built in from launch.</p><p id>This lets you set up and run powerful push notification campaigns to drive revenue, such as <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/blog/recover-abandoned-carts-with-push-notifications" id>abandoned cart notifications</a> (which can drive tens of thousands in monthly revenue for your brand, on autopilot).</p><figure id class="w-richtext-figure-type-image w-richtext-align-center" data-rt-type="image" data-rt-align="center"><div id><img src="https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/63894f0e251e567f6e443bfa/6785e5bb396725500c3b8d15_6785e30f31040572e940f842_john%2520varvatos%2520push%2520badge%2520top.avif" loading="lazy" alt="__wf_reserved_inherit" width="auto" height="auto" id></div></figure><p id>The best part is, it's fully managed.</p><p id>There's nothing for you to do but test your apps and give approval after we build them.</p><p id>We handle the build, app store publishing, and technical maintenance and updates after you launch.</p><p id>For a low upfront cost, and a small monthly fee, you can build an app that drives <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/ecom-app-revenue-calculator" id>five figures in revenue</a> for your brand each month, with no extra weight added to your workflow.</p><blockquote id>Ready to learn more? <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/demo" id>Book a free consultation</a> to discuss your project with one of our eCommerce app experts.</blockquote><h2 id>Zoho Commerce to Mobile App in Five Steps</h2><p id>MobiLoud lets you launch the perfect mobile apps for your Zoho&nbsp;Commerce brand, without extensive rebuilding, a massive investment, or limiting templates.</p><p id>There's virtually no downside, with the upside of higher mobile AOV, higher mobile conversion rate, and increased retention and customer LTV.</p><p id>Here are the five steps you'll go through to turn your Zoho Commerce store into an app.</p><h3 id>Step One: Book a Kickoff Call</h3><p id>Start with a <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/demo" id>consultation call</a>, where we'll walk you through the process, and show you what MobiLoud can do.</p><p id>You can get all your questions answered before you start, and share any unique needs or desires you have for the app with our team.</p><h3 id>Step Two: Choose a Plan</h3><p id>If you're happy to move ahead, choose the <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/pricing" id>plan</a> that suits your needs.</p><p id>All plans come with unlimited push notifications, done-for-you app configuration, full white-labeling, and start from just a few hundred per month with no long-term commitments or contracts.</p><h3 id>Step Three: Pass Off to Our Team</h3><p id>Ready to start? Just hand off the project to our team and we'll start building.</p><p id>As long as your mobile website is fast, user-friendly and responsive, our team will have no trouble turning it into high-quality mobile apps.</p><p id>We do all the work to write native code that turns your site into legitimate mobile apps. All you need to do is wait.</p><h3 id>Step Four: Test Your Apps</h3><p id>In approximately two weeks, your apps should be ready for testing.</p><p id>You can try out the apps on your own devices, send any feedback our way, and we'll work with that feedback to build the final version ready for launch.</p><h3 id>Step&nbsp;Five:&nbsp;Launch</h3><p id>Within a month, you'll be ready to go live.</p><p id>Our team handles the app store submission process for you, including all back-and-forths with the app stores to ensure your listings go live without a hitch.</p><p id>Outside of this, you can start promoting your mobile apps on your website, to your email list and on any other active channels, to start building momentum with your first app users.</p><figure id class="w-richtext-figure-type-image w-richtext-align-fullwidth" style="max-width:2240px" data-rt-type="image" data-rt-align="fullwidth" data-rt-max-width="2240px"><div id><img src="https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/63894f0e251e567f6e443bfa/6865a4f352326f55503677f1_20250702T0915-c2436afb-af62-4680-adc3-802e5704fff4.webp" loading="lazy" alt="__wf_reserved_inherit" width="auto" height="auto" id></div></figure><p id>In less than a month, you brand will be in the app stores, alongside some of the world's biggest brands and retailers - with minimal time, money and effort invested.</p><blockquote id>Ready to enjoy the benefits of having your own, branded eCommerce app? <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/demo" id>Book a free consultation now</a>!</blockquote><h2 id>Convert Your Zoho Commerce Store Into a Mobile App&nbsp;Now</h2><p id>Online commerce is becoming more and more mobile-centric.</p><p id>Now is the perfect time to launch your own apps.</p><p id>Your brand can still be ahead of the curve, offering an app experience that your loyal customers will respond to by shopping more often, and buying more when they do.</p><p id>MobiLoud is the best way to go live with a mobile app for your store.</p><p id>For low-four figures upfront, a small monthly cost, and zero effort, you'll have iOS and Android apps that grow revenue, trust and authority for your brand.</p><p id>It's risk-free. All it costs is a day's sales, to create a powerful brand asset, that gives you control and a direct line to your audience.</p><p id>Get started today. <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/demo" id>Book a free consultation with our team</a>, and we'll walk you through each step of the process, and help you understand if MobiLoud is right for you.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <FAQSidebar faqs={faqs} />
  <FinalCTA />
  <Footer />
</Layout>